Transmissible spongiform encephalopathies (TSEs) or prion diseases are neurodegenerative diseases that affect mammals. Examples of TSEs include sheep scrapie, bovine spongiform encephalopathy, chronic wasting disease of cervids and Creutzfeldt to Jakob disease (CJD) in humans. TSEs are associated with the accumulation of an abnormal and protease-resistant aggregate of prion protein (PrP) known as PrP-res or PrPSc
